"{\"uid\": \"cityam.com-five-cocktails-to-celebrate-the-olympics-and-their-host-city-paris\", \"text\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.  Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.  Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.  By:Simon Thomson  With temperatures set to soar to the late-twenties over the next few days and theOlympicson television, these simple yet sophisticated home cocktails are the ideal accompaniment for your ongoing summer of sport.  So grab a glass, gather your friends, and let the games begin.  The French 75  This is a Parisian classic. Originally a gin cocktail, it was created by legendary barman Harry MacElhone at the New York Bar in Paris during the First World War. He called it the 75 because it packed the punch of a French 75mm field gun. This version replaces the gin with Cognac for an even Frencher 75.  Ingredients\\u00a3 45ml R\\u00e9my Martin\\u00a3 1738 Accord Royal Cognac\\u00a3 15ml simple syrup\\u00a3 15ml lemon juice\\u00a3 Champagne  Stay ahead with our three daily briefings delivering all the key market moves, top business and political stories, and incisive analysis straight to your inbox.  Method\\u00a3 In a shaker, combine Cognac, simple syrup, lemon juice, and ice.\\u00a3 Shake and strain into a coupe.\\u00a3 Top with champagne.\\u00a3 Garnish with a lemon twist.  Mojito  The Olympics are a celebration of sporting excellence and our global community. Tap into the cosmopolitan carnival spirit with this thirst quenching tropical twist on the ever popular mojito.  Ingredients\\u00a3 30ml Mount Gay Eclipse Navy\\u00a3 Strength Rum\\u00a3 30ml fresh lime juice\\u00a3 60ml young coconut water\\u00a3 2tsp brown sugar\\u00a3 10 mint leaves  Method\\u00a3 Muddle mint leaves and brown sugar in the bottom of a shaker.\\u00a3 Add rum, lime, and stir.\\u00a3 Pour into Collins or Highball glass.\\u00a3 Add coconut water, top-up with crushed ice, and garnish with mint.  Suntory -196  The 2020 Tokyo Olympics were derailed by Covid. When they finally did take place in 2021, international visitors could not attend. They could not experience Tokyo's vibrant cocktail scene, its bustling izakayas serving whisky highballs on tap, or sample its vending machines offering an endless variety of ready to drink \\\"ch\\u016bhai\\\" cocktails.  Fortunately, you can now make up for this missed opportunity with Suntory -196. This convenient, refreshing pre-mix is made by freezing fruit in liquid nitrogen at -196\\u00b0C. The frozen fruit is crushed and macerated in vodka to extract the flavour, then strained and blended with the traditional Japanese spirit sh\\u014dch\\u016b and soda water before it is canned at 6% ABV. Available in lemon or grapefruit from Co-Op, Nisa, or WH Smith. Drink it ice cold.  Old fashioned  Relive the memories of London 2012 with an east London Old Fashioned made with brandy from Walthamstow distillery, Burnt Faith. Their limited edition Bourbon cask-aged brandy is a nod to the Old Fashioned's origins as a whiskey cocktail, and brings bags of rich, toffee apple flavour.  Ingredients\\u00a3 45ml Burnt Faith Brandy LimitedEdition Bourbon Cask\\u00a3 1 Sugar cube\\u00a3 Few dashes Angostura Cocoa Bitters Few dashes plain water  Method\\u00a3 Place a sugar cube in old fashioned glass and saturate with bitters.\\u00a3 Add a few dashes of plain water, and muddle until dissolved.\\u00a3 Fill the glass with ice cubes, add brandy, and stir gently.\\u00a3 Garnish with an orange slice, and a cocktail cherry.  PalomaThis features muscat wine aged in French oak barrels, and a blend of rose petals, herbs, and spices. These create a complex, floral drink with notes of rose, bay, and baking spices.  Ingredients:\\u00a3 50ml Metaxa 5 Stars\\u00a3 10ml lime juice\\u00a3 1tsp honey\\u00a3 60ml grapefruit soda  Method\\u00a3 Pour Metaxa into a Collins or highball glass.\\u00a3 Add lime juice and honey, and stir until dissolved.\\u00a3 Add ice, top up with grapefruit soda, then Garnish with a fresh grapefruit wedge.  Read more:The Olympics are about building a better world, not just muscles  Read more:Against the Olympics: Why we should stop worshipping elite sport  Share this article  Subscribe to the City AM newsletter to have our top stories delivered directly to your inbox.  Follow us for breaking news and latest updates\"}"